President Obama called First Vice President of Sudan, Salva Kiir, to discuss the status of peace negotiations and emphasize the United States' commitment to a peaceful and on-time referendum on Southern Sudanese self-determination. The President commended Vice President Kiir's leadership during this critical time in Sudan's history and urged him to engage with the National Congress Party to resolve outstanding issues related to the Comprehensive Peace Agreement (CPA) implementation and prevent violence. The two leaders agreed to continue the dialogue on the United States and the future of Southern Sudan.